    <!-- Phase 1: Verify Tables Exist -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-1-verify">🔍 Phase 1: Verify Tables Exist (Table Presence Check)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge complete">✅ COMPLETE - Dec 26 21:53 UTC</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Database queries to verify table presence in ENCY database</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Act.:</strong> 8 minutes</p>
            <p><strong>Result:</strong> 8 AI Chat tables created successfully (were missing, manual creation executed)</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Tasks</h3>
        
        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.1: Connect to Database</h4>
            <ul>
                <li>Open MySQL/MariaDB client or Admin Console in Comserv</li>
                <li>Select ENCY database</li>
                <li>Verify database connection is active</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.2: List All AI Chat Tables</h4>
            <p><strong>Execute Command:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SHOW TABLES LIKE 'ai%' OR LIKE 'documentation%' OR LIKE 'code_search%' OR LIKE 'web_search%';</code></pre>
            
            <p><strong>Expected Tables (6 total):</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ <code>ai_conversations</code> - Parent for all messages</li>
                <li>✓ <code>ai_messages</code> - Individual chat messages</li>
                <li>✓ <code>ai_model_config</code> - Model configuration per role/agent</li>
                <li>✓ <code>documentation_metadata_index</code> - Documentation search index</li>
                <li>✓ <code>code_search_index</code> - Code search index</li>
                <li>✓ <code>web_search_results</code> - Web search results storage</li>
                <li>✓ <code>documentation_role_access</code> - Access control rules</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p><strong>Record Results:</strong> Which tables exist? Which are missing? If any missing, note them for Phase 5.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 1.3: Check Startup Logs</h4>
            <p>Review application startup logs to see if tables were auto-created:</p>
            <pre><code>tail -f root/log/starman.log | grep -i "ai_chat\|schema\|create"</code></pre>
            
            <p><strong>Expected Log Output:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>[2025-12-26 ...] _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Creating table 'ai_conversations' ...
[2025-12-26 ...] _initialize_ai_chat_schema - Creating table 'ai_messages' ...
[2025-12-26 ...] _initialize_ai_chat_schema - All AI Chat tables created successfully.</code></pre>
            
            <p><strong>Record Results:</strong> Were tables auto-created on startup? Check logs for creation status.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="alert alert-success" style="margin-top: 15px;">
            <h4>✅ Phase 1 Results Summary</h4>
            <p><strong>All 8 AI Chat tables successfully created:</strong></p>
            <ul style="margin: 5px 0; column-count: 2;">
                <li>✅ ai_conversations (5 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ ai_messages (16 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ documentation_metadata_index (11 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ code_search_index (9 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ web_search_results (13 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ ai_model_config (15 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ documentation_role_access (4 cols)</li>
                <li>✅ ai_chat_context (4 cols)</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>Critical Finding:</strong> Tables were missing because auto-creation on startup is not implemented. Code changes needed in Comserv.pm to call DBSchemaManager during initialization.</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 2: Validate Structures -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-2-structure">📋 Phase 2: Validate Table Structures (Schema Validation)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge complete">✅ COMPLETE - Dec 26 21:55 UTC</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Verify table columns match Result class definitions</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Act.:</strong> 2 minutes</p>
            <p><strong>Result:</strong> All 3 critical tables validated - columns and types match Result class definitions exactly</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Critical Tables to Validate</h3>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.1: Validate ai_messages Table</h4>
            <p><strong>Command:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>DESCRIBE ai_messages;</code></pre>
            
            <p><strong>Expected Columns (18 total, from AiMessage.pm):</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>id (INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT)</li>
                <li>conversation_id (INT, FOREIGN KEY)</li>
                <li>user_id (INT, FOREIGN KEY)</li>
                <li>content (LONGTEXT)</li>
                <li>role (ENUM: 'user', 'assistant')</li>
                <li>agent_type (VARCHAR)</li>
                <li>model_used (VARCHAR)</li>
                <li>search_context (JSON)</li>
                <li>sources_cited (JSON)</li>
                <li>response_time_ms (INT)</li>
                <li>token_count (INT)</li>
                <li>created_at (DATETIME)</li>
                <li>updated_at (DATETIME)</li>
                <li>+ metadata fields</li>
            </ul>
            
            <p style="color: #721c24; background: #f8d7da; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px;">
                <strong>Action If Mismatch:</strong> Document differences. If columns missing, note for Phase 5 (schema fix needed).
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.2: Validate documentation_metadata_index Table</h4>
            <p><strong>Command:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>DESCRIBE documentation_metadata_index;</code></pre>
            
            <p><strong>Expected Columns (11 total):</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>id (INT PRIMARY KEY)</li>
                <li>file_path (VARCHAR UNIQUE)</li>
                <li>file_type (VARCHAR)</li>
                <li>title (VARCHAR)</li>
                <li>excerpt (TEXT)</li>
                <li>searchable_text (LONGTEXT FULLTEXT)</li>
                <li>content_hash (VARCHAR)</li>
                <li>role_access (VARCHAR)</li>
                <li>indexed_at (DATETIME)</li>
                <li>last_file_modified (DATETIME)</li>
                <li>file_size (INT)</li>
            </ul>

            <p><strong>Verify FULLTEXT Index:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SHOW INDEX FROM documentation_metadata_index WHERE Key_name = 'idx_searchable';</code></pre>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 2.3: Quick Spot-Check Other Tables</h4>
            <ul>
                <li><code>DESCRIBE code_search_index;</code> - Should have: id, file_path, code_elements(JSON), searchable_code, indexed_at</li>
                <li><code>DESCRIBE web_search_results;</code> - Should have: id, query, result_title, result_url, found_by_user_id, created_at</li>
                <li><code>DESCRIBE ai_model_config;</code> - Should have: id, role, agent_type, model_name, enabled, api_endpoint, temperature, max_tokens</li>
            </ul>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 3: Test Message Persistence -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-3-test-save">💾 Phase 3: Test Message Persistence (Write & Read Test)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge pending">EXECUTE TODAY - CRITICAL</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Manual test of chat message save/load cycle</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Est.:</strong> 45 minutes</p>
        </div>

        <h3>The Core Question This Phase Answers</h3>
        <p style="font-size: 16px; font-weight: bold; color: #004085; background: #cce5ff; padding: 12px; border-radius: 4px; margin: 15px 0;">
            <strong>❓ When I chat with the AI, are the messages actually being saved to the database, or just stored in memory?</strong>
        </p>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.1: Manual Test - Create a Test Conversation</h4>
            <p><strong>Steps:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Open the AI Chat interface in Comserv (http://localhost:5000/ai or /Documentation/AI)</li>
                <li>Create a new conversation with a test message</li>
                <li>Send a message like: "Test message from Dec 26 daily plan verification at [HH:MM:SS]"</li>
                <li>Note the EXACT timestamp and message content</li>
                <li>Wait for response from AI</li>
                <li>Verify message appears in chat history</li>
            </ol>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.2: Check Database for Saved Message</h4>
            <p><strong>Immediately After Chat:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>-- Find the conversation we just created
SELECT id, user_id, created_at FROM ai_conversations 
ORDER BY created_at DESC LIMIT 1;

-- Check conversation ID (let's say it's ID 1):
SELECT id, conversation_id, role, LEFT(content, 100) as content_preview, created_at 
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE conversation_id = 1 
ORDER BY created_at DESC;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Expected Result:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ Should find the conversation in ai_conversations table</li>
                <li>✓ Should find both user message and assistant response in ai_messages</li>
                <li>✓ Timestamps should be recent (within last 5 minutes)</li>
                <li>✓ Message content should match what you sent</li>
            </ul>

            <p style="color: #721c24; background: #f8d7da; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <strong>⚠️ CRITICAL:</strong> If messages don't appear in database, the AI Chat system is not persisting data. This must be fixed before proceeding.
            </p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.3: Verify Message Integrity</h4>
            <p><strong>Check that all fields are properly populated:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, conversation_id, user_id, role, content, agent_type, 
       model_used, search_context, sources_cited, created_at, updated_at
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE conversation_id = [YOUR_CONVERSATION_ID] 
LIMIT 1\G</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li>✓ role is 'user' or 'assistant' (not null)</li>
                <li>✓ content is not null or empty</li>
                <li>✓ agent_type populated (if assistant message)</li>
                <li>✓ model_used populated (if assistant message)</li>
                <li>✓ created_at and updated_at are set</li>
                <li>✓ search_context and sources_cited are JSON or null (not broken)</li>
            </ul>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 3.4: Test Conversation Reload</h4>
            <p><strong>Test that messages persist across page reloads:</strong></p>
            <ol>
                <li>Note the conversation ID from task 3.2</li>
                <li>Refresh the page (Ctrl+R or browser reload)</li>
                <li>Navigate back to the conversation</li>
                <li>Verify all messages still appear in the UI</li>
                <li>Verify message order is correct (oldest first, newest last)</li>
            </ol>

            <p style="color: #155724; background: #d4edda; padding: 10px; border-radius: 3px; margin-top: 10px;">
                <strong>✅ Success:</strong> If messages persist after reload, data persistence is working correctly.
            </p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Phase 4: Query Testing -->
    <div class="content-section">
        <h2 id="phase-4-query-test">🔎 Phase 4: Query & Retrieval Testing (Search & Filtering)</h2>

        <div class="phase-status">
            <span class="status-badge pending">EXECUTE TODAY - IF PHASE 3 PASSES</span>
            <p><strong>Execution:</strong> Test that queries work correctly on saved data</p>
            <p><strong>Duration Est.:</strong> 20 minutes</p>
        </div>

        <h3>Tasks</h3>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.1: Test Conversation History Retrieval</h4>
            <p><strong>Query all messages in a conversation:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, role, LEFT(content, 80) as content_preview, created_at
FROM ai_messages 
WHERE conversation_id = [ID]
ORDER BY created_at ASC;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> Messages return in chronological order, all fields present</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.2: Test User's Message Count</h4>
            <p><strong>Get count of user's messages:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT user_id, COUNT(*) as message_count, 
       MAX(created_at) as last_message
FROM ai_messages 
GROUP BY user_id
HAVING user_id = [YOUR_USER_ID];</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> Count matches number of messages you sent in testing</p>
        </div>

        <div class="task-card">
            <h4>Task 4.3: Test Documentation Index Search (Optional)</h4>
            <p><strong>If documentation indexing is active, test FULLTEXT search:</strong></p>
            <pre><code>SELECT id, file_path, MATCH(searchable_text) AGAINST('test' IN BOOLEAN MODE) as score
FROM documentation_metadata_index 
WHERE MATCH(searchable_text) AGAINST('test' IN BOOLEAN MODE)
LIMIT 5;</code></pre>

            <p><strong>Verify:</strong> FULLTEXT search returns results with relevance scores</p>
        </div>
    </div>

